ontrolValue        //in\r\n)\n"})}),"\n",(0,i.jsx)(n.h2,{id:"description",children:"Description"}),"\n",(0,i.jsxs)(n.p,{children:["This function allows you to control a setting of a Model Finder context, one (or all) of the models contained therein, or a Model Finder result buffer. These settings control the execution of ",(0,i.jsx)(n.a,{href:"/DOC_PUBLIC_AIL11_MD_HELP_SOURCE/Reference/mod/MmodFind",children:(0,i.jsx)(n.code,{children:"MmodFind"})})," operations. Most of the control type settings can be inquired using ",(0,i.jsx)(n.a,{href:"/DOC_PUBLIC_AIL11_MD_HELP_SOURCE/Reference/mod/MmodInquire",children:(0,i.jsx)(n.code,{children:"MmodInquire"})}),"."]}),"\n",(0,i.jsx)(n.p,{children:"The units in which you should provide values (for example, position and width), depend on the model and context that you are using. In general, provide values as follows:"}),"\n",(0,i.jsxs)(n.ul,{children:["\n",(0,i.jsxs)(n.li,{children:["For a non-synthetic model, provide values in the pixel coordinate system, even if the target is calibrated. The only exception is when specifying angles (for example, ",(0,i.jsx)(n.a,{href:"/DOC_PUBLIC_AIL11_MD_HELP_SOURCE/Reference/mod/MmodControl",children:(0,i.jsx)(n.code,{children:"M_REFERENCE_ANGLE"})}),"); in these cases, you must specify the angles in the relative coordinate system if the target is calibrated."]}),"\n",(0,i.jsxs)(n.li,{children:["For a synthetic model in an ",(0,i.jsx)(n.a,{href:"/DOC_PUBLIC_AIL11_MD_HELP_SOURCE/Reference/mod/MmodAlloc",children:(0,i.jsx)(n.code,{children:"M_GEOMETRIC"})})," or ",(0,i.jsx)(n.a,{href:"/DOC_PUBLIC_AIL11_MD_HELP_SOURCE/Reference/mod/MmodAlloc",children:(0,i.jsx)(n.code,{children:"M_GEOMETRIC_CONTROLLED"})})," context, provide values in the user-defined units for the model; their relationship to pixels is defined using ",(0,i.jsx)(n.a,{href:"/DOC_PUBLIC_AIL11_MD_HELP_SOURCE/Reference/mod/MmodControl",children:(0,i.jsx)(n.code,{children:"MmodControl"})})," with ",(0,i.jsx)(n.a,{href:"/DOC_PUBLIC